    element.style.transform = 'translateY(-4px) scale(1.02)';
}

function exitFlowState(element) {
    flowStateActive = false;
    element.style.borderColor = '';
    element.style.boxShadow = '';
    element.style.transform = '';
}
```

### Accessibility & Consciousness Integration

**Reduced Motion Respect**:
```css
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    * {
        animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
        transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    }
}
```

**High Contrast Consciousness**:
```css
@media (prefers-contrast: high) {
    :root {
        --moksha-flowing-gray-500: #4B5563;
        --ubuntu-collective-blue-500: #1E40AF;
    }
}
```

### Status Indicator Patterns

**Consciousness State Indicators**:
```css
.status-moksha {
    background: var(--nirvana-enlightened-green-100);
    color: var(--nirvana-enlightened-green-700);
    padding: var(--breathe-1) var(--breathe-3);
    border-radius: 20px;
    font-weight: 500;
}

.status-flow {
    background: var(--flow-state-amber-100);
    color: var(--flow-state-amber-700);
}

.status-ubuntu {
    background: var(--ubuntu-collective-blue-100);
    color: var(--ubuntu-collective-blue-700);
}
```

### Implementation Best Practices

1. **Token Organization**: Group by spiritual concept, then by element type
2. **Naming Convention**: Use descriptive spiritual terms that convey meaning
3. **Fallback Strategy**: Always provide fallback colors for browser compatibility
4. **Documentation**: Include spiritual context in comments for team understanding
5. **Testing**: Verify consciousness states across different devices and preferences

### File Structure Pattern
```
/design-system/
  ├── design-tokens.json          # Master token specification
  ├── css/
  │   ├── tokens.css             # CSS custom properties
  │   ├── components.css         # Component patterns
  │   └── utilities.css          # Utility classes
  ├── docs/
  │   ├── showcase.html          # Live documentation
  │   └── reference.md           # Implementation guide
  └── integrations/
      ├── tailwind.config.js     # Tailwind integration
      └── react-components.tsx   # React patterns
```

This pattern successfully bridges spiritual wisdom with practical design implementation, creating maintainable and meaningful design systems.

